  <p>It was announced through the National Survey of Construction Companies (ENEC for its Spanish acronym), that the construction sector grew 6.1% on the first half of 2022. For November 2022, the production value of construction companies grew 2.5% when compared to October, adding three months of growth, mainly driven by the construction of industrial properties as a result of nearshoring. </p>

  <p>Regarding the mortgage interest rates, the Director of INFONAVIT said that there is no intention to increase interest rates in line with the inflation, in contrast to commercial banks, with the objective of increasing the access to home among the lower income segments. </p>

  <p>In order to meet the housing needs of its affiliates, INFONAVIT announced an increase in the maximum amount available for a mortgage loan, to approximately MXN 2.4 million, which coupled with the increase in the maximum age the affiliates can apply for a loan, from 65 to 70 years, and the start of FOVISSSTE's continuous inscription model, which allow the affiliates to apply for a mortgage at any time, will contribute to improve the dynamism of the housing sector. </p>

